endpoint.response:
data.resources[] : per resource 'users', `fields[]` ora include, oltre a
email/locale/roles/password, le 11 chiavi:
  { key: "personal_data.type",        type: "select",     group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.title",       type: "select",     group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.first_name",  type: "text",       group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.last_name",   type: "text",       group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.company_name",type: "text",       group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.tax_code",    type: "text",       group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.vat_number",  type: "text",       group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.sdi_code",    type: "text",       group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.birth_date",  type: "date",       group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.contacts",    type: "collection", group: "personal_data" }
  { key: "personal_data.addresses",   type: "collection", group: "personal_data" }
(D5) OGNI field entry porta anche `mandatory: bool`. Set mandatory=true:
email, locale, password, personal_data.type, personal_data.first_name,
personal_data.last_name, personal_data.company_name (users); name (roles).
Tutti gli altri mandatory=false. Anche `GET /api/meta/{resource}` (data.fields)
emette `mandatory`.
